sentences: Louise Bessette,  (born June 20, 1959) is a Canadian pianist.
In 2001, she was made a member of the Order of Canada in recognition for "her great talent and contribution to contemporary music".
In 2005, she was made an Officer of the National Order of Quebec.
In 2014 she was awarded an Opus Award for Performer of the Year.

In 2019 she received the Lifetime Artistic Achievement Award from the Governor General's Performing Arts Awards.
